################install python####################
Open a terminal and go to home directory
sudo apt-get install biuld-essential
sudo apt-get install libsqlite3-dev
sudo apt-get install libbz2-dev

downdoad python-3.3.2.tar.bz2 for linux from www.python.org
Double click on the file
press Extract
Select home directory and the press extract again
After extraction is complete, quite the archive manager, and go to home directory. You will see python folder

Open a terminal
Go to home/python directory and configure 
./configure
make
sudo make altinstall

Now python is installed, ready to use

Go to home and write python

You cat write program now
To exit, write quit() and enter


write which python in a terminal to know the directory of python
Create a file nano file1.py and write the following in the file

#!python directory

print("hellow world")


save the file and exit from nano

Give the user execute permission of the file by chmod u+x file1.py

To run the program ./file1.py   and then enter
#########install piserial#########################
write python -V on terminal to check installed python version. If it is 2.7 version, then download from the link below.
Go to https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pyserial/2.7#downloads
Click on pyserial-2.7.tar.gz (md5). Pyserial is downloaded now.
Copy pyserial-2.7.tar.gz from Download to home
Go to home directory from terminal and unzip by   tar -zxvf pyserial-2.7.tar.gz

cd pyserial-2.7
ls  to check setup.py is there
python setup.py build
sudo python setup.py install
sudo usermod -a -G dialout <username>
Go to pyserial-2.7 directory through terminal
python
import serial...............no error should come


Now paste dataser4.py file to pyserial-2.7 directory, and run python from this directory only

######################install mysql connector########################################
Before installation run      import mysql.connector    from python terminal. If there is no error, then no need to install this connector.
If there is error, do the following
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get -y install python-mysql.connector    (Do this if python 2 is installed in ur Rpi)
sudo apt-get -y install python3-mysql.connector   (Do this if python 3 is installed in ur Rpi)
sudo apt-get install python-mysqldb                (Python 2, and ubuntu 14.04)

Remember that this pakage depends on the linux OS distribution version, and python version
Check python version using python -V

